1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the governance framework by which the Elko County Information Operations Department identifies,
 logs,
 triages,
 and routes IT service improvement opportunities.
 This policy defines the Service Improvement Register as the authoritative record of improvement intake and triage activity,
 and the Service Improvement Plan as the initiation document for improvement initiatives that qualify for formal project designation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.14"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 It establishes the Assistant IT Director as the owner of the improvement intake function and defines the conditions under which improvement work routes to the standard work order system or to formal project management.
\end_layout

